reviews_data.review_text: Great vibe and great coffee!
Great service, atmosphere, and food. Highly recommended!

Genuinely my favorite Cafe in Waxhaw. The prices are good and the food/drinks are great! It's my go to spot to meet friends, or do some remote work.

Parking is nice and it's a fairly easy place to get in and out of. 100% recommend!
Amazing employees are and coffee was delicious!
Great coffee and service! We also got some beans to take home (also delicious).

I just went and it was very nice! Super sweet staff, very tasty drinks and a quaint atmosphere. My brother got a smoothie, and one of the staff noticed it may have been made wrong and automatically offered to remake it. It was really nice and my brother appreciated it, since he would normally not ask. I recommend going, I know my family and I will likely come back to try to house special next time!
Beautiful coffee shop! I'm so happy I can support my fellow Africans! Wonderful customer service with quality and fresh food products !
Nice and cozy!!!
Best Vanilla Latte will be back for more
The vibe at Jebena Cafe is so lovely. I love the music they play and the fall decor! The two young girls that took my order were so sweet! They made me a delicious cappuccino!!
Really good coffee , 100% recommend!

Jelena will blow you away - authentic Ethiopian beans, homemade pastries & yummy from scratch cookies - best coffee in the heart of downtown Waxhaw  loved their bagels too. Absolutely recommend this gem - David & his wife (owners) are so warm, welcoming & hospitable - such an incredible delight to my wife & I.
Great service and delicious drinks!
Great coffee
Wonderful family owned cafe!
Best cold brew coffee around.

I've been wanting to try Jebena for a while now. And it does not disappoint and is a hidden gem in downtown Waxhaw!!!! I've been here a few times since coming here with my family and everything I have tried has been amazing. The atmosphere is inviting and the staff is super friendly.

The croissant is fresh, buttery, and flakey. Their smoothies are very flavorful and delicious. Plus, their coffee had rich flavors and has just the right amount between coffee and flavor you chose. I've had both the Carmel frappe and the iced mocha and would definitely get them again.

If you haven't tried them already you definitely should!!!
Absolutely the best caffe mocha I've ever had.  It actually tasted like coffee (good dark coffee too) and real cocoa, not too sweet and richly flavored.  Very cool vibe too, really enjoyed it!!
Very nice owners and super rich coffee
This place is a hidden gem in Waxhaw!! Got to know about it only today.. the matcha latte tasted so good! I'm going back for sure!

I went to Jebena with friends today. The food was beyond delicious and the owner was so friendly. You could tell he really cared about his food. Looking forward to going back soon. I would highly recommend this cage to everyone.

Great place to grab a coffee, sandwich/salad & work. It's quiet & the atmosphere is very relaxed. Their team is extremely thoughtful & does such a great job of checking in on you, even after you leave the counter.
Coffee was phenomenal!
Heard great things and they're all true! Not much to leave a review but service was amazing and the environment was very calm after the storm knocked out my internet. Very friendly and great drinks!
We really love the coffee, pastries, sandwiches, food and wonderful service at this new Cafe in Waxhaw.
Great place to chill, great coffee and wonderful staff. David was very cool and we had a good talk with him. Will definitely visit again.
This place is amazing! I've been here a couple of times and ordered different items, and each time I wasn't disappointed :D I especially like the tuna croissant and beef shawarma wrap.
This place is super cute! I love this new addition to downtown Waxhaw! The drinks and food are great, I love the atmosphere, and everyone is super friendly!

I tried out Jebena Cafe today and I'm so glad! Croissants are large, buttery & flaky and the coffee is amazing. I got an iced vanilla latte and loved that you can still really taste the coffee even with the vanilla flavoring. The atmosphere is inviting & the owners are very friendly! Also, there are outlets around many of the tables, so if you need somewhere to do work/schoolwork this is a good spot. I will definitely be back!
The staff were so friendly and welcoming. The staff will definitely put a smile on your face. Highly recommend their ice latte and warmed croissant with a side of butter.
What a great place for food and coffee with an added bonus of amazing staff! The staff treat you like family not just another customer coming in. You definitely have to try this place out! :)

Jebena Cafe is a great addition to Downtown Waxhaw. The Cafe is located on the corner of N Church Street and Price Street. Stop in to start your day with an amazing cup of Ethiopian coffee. You can also get croissants, sandwiches, and gelato at the Cafe. I ordered a croissant, which was delicious . The cup of coffee tasted rich and bold and definitely woke me up that morning. If you enjoy drinking a magnificent cup of coffee, go to Jebena. Your tast buds will thank you.
Great

**Incredible Coffee Experience!**
My husband and I visit every Sunday, and it's always a delight. I usually get a peppermint iced coffee, while he enjoys a classic black coffee. Their tiramisu is simply delicious! We were pleasantly surprised at how affordable our coffee was, and we even ended up purchasing coffee beans to enjoy at home. Highly recommend!
Great coffee and friendly service

Stopped by for a coffee and croissant. Coffee is good, croissant is stale. Gave it back to be discarded and told the owner it was inedible. He asked if I wanted a fresh one. Unbelievable. Won't be back.

I think their food is a very and good quality!!
The Greek salad David fixed for me was excellent!
Quality food and customer service! Everything on the menu tastes amazing!!
Found this little place by accident and so glad I did.  The service was quick and friendly. The coffee was flavorful and the croissants were delightfully light and buttery.  I will be back!!
A great cup of coffee, food looked delicious, bright atmosphere. Can't wait to go back. Our new coffee spot in Waxhaw for sure.
Had a great cup of coffee and learned about the Jebena ceremony. A welcoming place for friends and others.

I just had the most delightful experience at Jebena Cafe in Waxhaw! I'd been wanting to try it for a while, and let me tell you, it did not disappoint.

The atmosphere is warm and inviting. It's not a huge place, but it has a cozy vibe that makes you feel right at home. I went for a lunchtime visit, and there were a few people catching up with friends over steaming cups of coffee, while others were focused on laptops.

Speaking of coffee, that's definitely the star of the show here. I opted for a traditional Ethiopian brew, and it was unlike any coffee I'd ever had before. Rich, complex, and aromatic - it was a true flavor explosion. They even have the whole brewing ceremony on display, which was fascinating to watch.

For food, I went with the chicken salad croissant. It sounds simple, but the flavors were fantastic. The chicken salad was perfectly seasoned and packed with fresh ingredients, and the croissant itself was buttery and flaky. The portions were generous, and I left feeling happy and satisfied.

The staff at Jebena Cafe were friendly and helpful. They were happy to answer my questions about the menu and the coffee brewing process.  Overall, it was a fantastic experience, and I can't wait to go back and try some of their other offerings.  If you're looking for a unique and delicious coffee experience in Waxhaw, Jebena Cafe is definitely worth checking out!

I recently had the opportunity to visit Jebena with friends, and it was a wonderful experience. The service was outstanding, and the food was delicious. My favorite aspect was the atmosphere, which was both relaxing and refreshing. The tiramisu and chocolate cake were particular highlights for me.
We got an iced latte and a smoothie and both were great.
I had croissant and coffee, it was amazing. The atmosphere is 10/10. Try their traditional coffee

We stopped in when I needed a coffee and got a cookie and some gelato as well. Coffee is super yummy (I'm a coffee snob) and cookie and gelato were delicious as well!

Will definitely come back another time!

I took a friend here for coffee for her birthday. Both of our coffees were very good. We did not try the desserts, but they looked very good as well. It was quiet, plenty of space, and nice decor. We recommend it!
Delicious frappuccinos! The staff are really friendly. They'll ask how your day is and genuinely care about the answer.
Drinks are amazing and the space is large and open.  Have come to get some work done, have had business meetings, and have come to just chill.  Friendly and inviting space!

I ordered their signature latte and curry chicken crossaint sandwich and both were delicious. Whether you're a coffee connoisseur or just looking for a cozy spot to relax, is a must-visit. Also a great place for a nice study spot!
David & Rahwa are very nice and their menu has something for everyone
Very nice place and good service
It's a wonderful cafe friendly staff fresh organic products and made with love go try it seriously you won't regret it at all

Prices are too high. I paid $4 for a mini chocolate chip cookie that was not good and my kid didn't like it at all. The lava cake was dried and the napoleon was not really a napoleon. Very  dissapointed and I'm Not coming back.

Great location for business meeting, personal chats with friends or just relaxing with some incredible coffee and food. We will be back for sure. This is an excellent addition to Waxhaw's small business community.
They forgot our food for 25 minutes. If you want your food you will have to remind them to give it to you. They gave me coffee instead of chai. Food was also cold when it came. Would not recommend.
Had wonderful tiramisu and Jabena coffee. Service was great. Enjoyed our coffee being served in special cups on ornate serving tray with incense burning at our table.
What a great new place to grab a coffee, pastry and sandwiches. Super cool people and the coffee was wonderful. Check them out and support our local businesses.
Happy to have here in waxhaw the lattes are really good quality and a fair price the staff is friendly- the pastries are a bit expensive compared to other places, but taste good!
They are really very professional when they serve you and the food is amazing, blessings
Friendly staff, welcoming vibe, great food (croissants to die for), great location.

This is a great new place to get a coffee. Awesome atmosphere, staff, and menu variety! The coffee is INCREDIBLE and tastes like the real thing, not like the processed fake crap from Starbucks. We also met the owner and he was so nice and welcoming to us. Cool aesthetic inside with comfortable seating, as well as natural lighting. This is a great opportunity to support a local business... come check them out!
Cute little place. Attentive staff. Best croissant I have ever had. (Lived in Europe so my standards are high).
Great new coffee shop! Staff very nice, only problem was they charged me $9.35 for a chocolate croissant. Not sure if mistake or inflation...
Very cute coffee shop with a great atmosphere. I see this becoming another local hangout spot with great drinks and service.
Just stopped by there the bakery goods are very good made fresh daily the coffee is excellent. The staff is very nice.
Great addition to Waxhaw, amazing place very relaxing
Everything was amazing .
Wonderful house black tea and delicious ham and cheese croissant.

My boyfriend Blake and I were walking around downtown Waxhaw after having dinner at Maxwell's and noticed this place. We decided it looked interesting and unique so we said why not check it out.  Great s'mores iced coffee and chocolate drizzle croissant.  My boyfriend had a mint cocoa which he thought was great.   They offered a complimentary croissant to try after we ordered and finished what we had.  Very friendly and helpful.  I would definitely recommend and check it out.  Nice and relaxing atmosphere too.
Cute and spacious spot! Good coffee, sandwiches and croissants. Workers are friendly :)
Love the coffee! Love the desserts. I tried both tiramisu and coconut cake and it was absolutely delicious. It was less sweet and moderately moist. It was perfect. Would recommend to everyone.
Cute place for coffee.  Service was great. I recommend the lavender cappuccino!
One of the best coffee place. Yummy treats. Much love to the amazing baristas who work here. You want find a faster, cleaner and peaceful coffee place in town.

Love this place!! The service is wonderful and the food is absolutely delicious! The strawberry croissant and ham sandwich on a croissant was absolutely phenomenal!! Love the family atmosphere the place gives off. I most definitely recommend!!
The most delicious chocolate chip cookie I have ever had! Love this addition to downtown WXW! Adorable inside and super yummy foods!
Amazing coffee, peaceful place to read great place to recommend.
Lovely cafe with great coffee, yummy treats and friendly service
We didn't try any food today, but the coffee was fantastic. The atmosphere was great as well. We will definitely be back to try more!!
